'''November 7''' is the 7th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}  the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}  day is {{ill|Taian|WD=Q96759844|1=taian}}{{efn|ja|大安|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|1=taian|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1306255}} . 

== Events ==
* {{ill|Shōryaku|en|Shōryaku|WD=Q1324858|lt=Shōryaku|1=Shōryaku}}  1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|990|en|990|WD=Q23730|lt=990|1=990}}  {{ill|November 26|en|November 26|WD=Q3019|lt=November 26|1=November 26}} ) – An era change was made from {{ill|Eiso (era)|en|Eiso (era)|WD=Q1327358|lt=Eizoku (Japan)|1=Eiso (era)}}  to {{ill|Shōryaku|en|Shōryaku|WD=Q1324858|lt=Shōryaku|1=Shōryaku}}  via {{ill|era change|ja|改元|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/era change|1=era change|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11498853}} .
* {{ill|Jianwu|en|Jianwu|WD=Q11065423|lt=Kenmu|1=Jianwu}}  3rd year / {{ill|Engen|1=Engen|2=ja|3=延元|WD=Q1194159|1=Engen|2=ja|3=延元|WD=Q1194159|ja|Engen|1=Engen|2=ja|3=延元|WD=Q1194159|1=Engen|2=ja|3=延元|WD=Q1194159|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engen|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1194159}}  1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|1336|en|1336|WD=Q6028|lt=1336|1=1336}}  {{ill|December 10|en|December 10|WD=Q2302|lt=December 10|1=December 10}} ) – {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|1=Ashikaga Takauji|2=ja|3=足利尊氏|ja|Ashikaga Takauji|1=Ashikaga Takauji|2=ja|3=足利尊氏|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga Takauji|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q297107}}  consulted with the brothers {{ill|Zeien|ja|是円|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zeien|1=Q84977487|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q84977487}}  and {{ill|Masae|ja|真恵|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Masae|1=Q85271929|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q85271929}} , and established the {{ill|Kenmu Shikimoku|ja|建武式目|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenmu Shikimoku|1=Kenmu Shikimoku|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q4226141}} . The {{ill|Muromachi Shogunate|ja|Ashikaga Shogunate|1=Ashikaga shogunate|2=ja|3=室町幕府|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Muromachi Shogunate|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1154406}}  was founded.
* {{ill|Kan'ei|en|Kan'ei|WD=Q1192913|lt=Kan'ei|1=Kan'ei}}  11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1634|en|1634|WD=Q6872|lt=1634|1=1634}}  {{ill|December 26|en|December 26|WD=Q2761|lt=December 26|1=December 26}} ) – An Iga vendetta incident occurred: Watanabe Kazuma dueled with Kawai Matagorō and others in a {{ill|Duel|en|Duel|WD=Q191503|lt=duel|1=Duel}} , with Araki Mataueimon assisting (in what became known as the {{ill|Igagoe vendetta|en|Igagoe vendetta|WD=Q10564180|lt=Kagiya no Tsuji Duel|1=Igagoe vendetta}} ).
* {{ill|Kaei|en|Kaei|WD=Q1146125|lt=Kaei|1=Kaei}}  6th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1853|en|1853|WD=Q7666|lt=1853|1=1853}}  {{ill|December 7|en|December 7|WD=Q2299|lt=December 7|1=December 7}} ) – The {{ill|Edo Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|1=Tokugawa shogunate|2=ja|3=江戸幕府|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo Shogunate|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}  appointed Nakahama Manjirō ({{ill|Nakahama Manjirō|en|Nakahama Manjirō|WD=Q1193167|lt=John Manjiro|1=Nakahama Manjirō}} ) to a construction role.
* {{ill|Kaei|en|Kaei|WD=Q1146125|lt=Kaei|1=Kaei}}  7th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1854|en|1854|WD=Q7670|lt=1854|1=1854}}  {{ill|December 26|en|December 26|WD=Q2761|lt=December 26|1=December 26}} ) – The {{ill|Toyoyo Strait Earthquake|ja|豊予海峡Earthquake|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyoyo Strait Earthquake|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}  occurred.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|WD=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}}  7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|1579|en|1579|WD=Q6709|lt=1579|1=1579}}  {{ill|November 25|en|November 25|WD=Q3020|lt=November 25|1=November 25}} ) – {{ill|Mōri Hidemoto|en|Mōri Hidemoto|WD=Q1133105|lt=Mōri Hidemoto|1=Mōri Hidemoto}} , lord of the {{ill|Chōfu Domain|en|Chōfu Domain|WD=Q903430|lt=Chōfu Domain|1=Chōfu Domain}}  (died {{ill|1650|en|1650|WD=Q6951|lt=1650|1=1650}} ).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Emperor Keikō|en|Emperor Keikō|WD=Q329723|lt=Keikō Tennō|1=Emperor Keikō}}  60th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|130|en|130|WD=Q396661|lt=130|1=130}}  {{ill|December 24|en|December 24|WD=Q2705|lt=December 24|1=December 24}} ) – {{ill|Emperor Keikō|en|Emperor Keikō|WD=Q329723|lt=Keikō Tennō|1=Emperor Keikō}} , the 12th {{ill|Emperor of Japan|en|Emperor of Japan|WD=Q208233|lt=Emperor|1=Emperor of Japan}}  and father of {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ヤマトタケル|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q461258}}  (born {{ill|1195|en|1195|WD=Q19745|lt=1195|1=1195}} ).
* {{ill|Kan'ei|en|Kan'ei|WD=Q1192913|lt=Kan'ei|1=Kan'ei}}  5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1628|en|1628|WD=Q6840|lt=1628|1=1628}}  {{ill|December 2|en|December 2|WD=Q2296|lt=December 2|1=December 2}} ) – {{ill|Mikogami Tenzen|en|Mikogami Tenzen|WD=Q6850068|lt=Ono Tadaaki|1=Mikogami Tenzen}} , a swordsman and instructor to the shogunal family.

